<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
ws_get_accept_value uses strlen and strncpy on the pointer ws_key_header expecting a NUL-terminated string. In ahc_cb the header value is obtained via MHD_lookup_connection_value_n which returns a pointer and an explicit key_size; ahc_cb only checks key_size == WS_KEY_LEN but does not ensure that the buffer is NUL-terminated. If the stored header value has length WS_KEY_LEN and is not followed by a terminating '\0' (i.e. pos->value is not NUL-terminated), strlen(ws_key_header) will read past the object bound and strncpy(str, key, WS_KEY_LEN + 1) will attempt to read WS_KEY_LEN+1 bytes from key, causing out-of-bounds access. Therefore Rule 21.17 is violated.
</scenario>
